The paper discusses machine learning models and their interpretability, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on causal questions and explanations suggests a connection to causal inference (cs.CE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR), as understanding the reasons behind a model's decisions can help identify potential vulnerabilities or biases. Finally, the mention of evaluation metrics suggests a connection to social and information networks (cs.SI), as measuring interpretability can be important in understanding how information spreads through networks.
